      <h2>The Honest Answer</h2>
      <p>How long it takes depends entirely on your daily practice time, your prior musical experience, and what you define as having learned harmonium. A complete beginner practicing 20-30 minutes daily can play simple bhajans in 4-6 weeks, complete Alankars 1-10 in 3 months, play a first raga adequately in 6 months, and perform intermediate-level music in 1-2 years. Advanced classical playing takes 5-10+ years of serious study.</p>

      <h2>Timeline With 20 Minutes Daily</h2>
      <p>Week 1 to 2: Learn all 7 swaras and play ascending descending scale. Week 3 to 6: First bhajan playable from memory. Month 2 to 3: All 10 alankars at moderate speed. Month 4 to 6: First raga (Yaman) with aroha avaroha and simple improvisation. Month 7 to 12: 5-10 bhajans plus 2-3 ragas. Year 2 onwards: Increasingly refined classical technique.</p>

      <h2>Factors That Speed Progress</h2>
      <p>Prior musical experience (pianists learn fingering much faster). Daily practice consistency (20 min daily beats 2 hours on weekends). Listening to Indian classical music regularly (develops ear and musical intuition). Singing swara names while practicing (builds ear-hand connection). Getting occasional feedback from an experienced player even if not taking formal lessons.</p>

      <h2>Common Progress Blockers</h2>
      <p>Practicing too fast before precision is established. Skipping alankars because they seem boring. Learning many songs superficially rather than mastering fewer deeply. Not developing ear training alongside physical technique. Inconsistent practice — breaks of more than 3 days reset significant muscle memory. Comparing progress to others rather than your own previous baseline.</p>

      <h2>Setting Realistic Expectations</h2>
      <p>Harmonium is genuinely learnable through self-study to intermediate level. The web harmonium at harmoniumhalt.com and our structured lessons are designed specifically for this self-directed path. Expect slow progress in the first 4 weeks then accelerating progress as fundamentals solidify. Most learners report a breakthrough moment around months 3-4 when the instrument suddenly feels natural.</p>

